input: Anne is blue. Anne is kind. Anne is nice. Anne is quiet. Anne is rough. Anne is young. Erin is red. Fiona is kind. Fiona is rough. Harry is kind. Harry is red. Harry is young. Quiet, red things are nice. If something is blue then it is young. All young things are kind. If Erin is nice and Erin is quiet then Erin is rough. If something is nice and quiet then it is blue. All red things are quiet. Question: Erin is kind.?
output:
universe u

constant obj : Type u

constant Anne : obj
constant Erin : obj
constant Fiona : obj
constant Harry : obj

constant Blue : obj → Prop
constant Kind : obj → Prop
constant Nice : obj → Prop
constant Quiet : obj → Prop
constant Rough : obj → Prop
constant Young : obj → Prop
constant Red : obj → Prop

axiom T1 : Blue Anne
axiom T2 : Kind Anne
axiom T3 : Nice Anne
axiom T4 : Quiet Anne
axiom T5 : Rough Anne
axiom T6 : Young Anne
axiom T7 : Red Erin
axiom T8 : Kind Fiona
axiom T9 : Rough Fiona
axiom T10 : Kind Harry
axiom T11 : Red Harry
axiom T12 : Young Harry

axiom R1 : ∀ x : obj, Quiet x ∧ Red x → Nice x
axiom R2 : ∀ x : obj, Blue x → Young x
axiom R3 : ∀ x : obj, Young x → Kind x
axiom R4 : Nice Erin ∧ Quiet Erin → Rough Erin
axiom R5 : ∀ x : obj, Nice x ∧ Quiet x → Blue x
axiom R6 : ∀ x : obj, Red x → Quiet x

theorem erin_is_kind : Kind Erin :=
begin
  apply R3,
  apply R2,
  apply R5 Erin,
  split,
  apply R1 Erin,
  split,
  exact T7,
  apply R6,
  exact T7,
  apply R6,
  exact T7,
end
